= For the very, very impatient

If you have WEBrick installed (which comes as standard with Ruby
1.8.2), then you can simply say

  ruby extras/webrick/rublog_servlet.rb

Once it starts, point your browser at http://localhost:8808 and you
should see documents describing RubLog.

= For the slightly less impatient

See the file doc/SimpleInstallation.rdoc.